{"questionId":"2967059","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math>, defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>A sketch of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is shown in the following diagram. Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> is the maximum point on this graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/25e5399ab1de5378ebe14753949a47e0a97efd82.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>S</mi></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use implicit differentiation and product rule&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; M1M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>S</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use implicit differentiation, product rule and chain rule&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> M1M1M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>S</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to make equation explicit to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use product rule and chain rule&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; M1M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>S</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>S</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></msup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>368</mn><mo> </mo><mi>S</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36789</mn><mo>…</mo><mo> </mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2967059","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.2h","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find, in terms of S, the x-coordinate of point A.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Max